collections.name: Mosaic Harmony
collections.description:
An artistic project that explores the complexity and beauty of life and existence through digital works, carefully printed using the Fine Art Giclée technique on 12-color cotton canvas with long-lasting pigments. These digital creations are transformed into physical artworks—original contemporary paintings. Each piece represents a fusion of colors and well-composed scenes, where the mosaic effect and the concept of "balanced composition" play a central role. A meticulous combination of details turns every painting into a visually synthesized experience.

The artworks in this collection are designed to create a strong chromatic and emotional impact, capturing the subtle and often invisible harmony that connects the elements of our daily existence. People, urban spaces, and nature intertwine in a mosaic of emotions and meaningful moments, offering a reflection on the inevitable connection between the elements of the reality that surrounds us.

collections.name: The World of Wayang
collections.description:
Wayang is a traditional performing art that uses leather puppets as a medium for performance. These puppets are made of buffalo or cow skin carved with intricate details and played by a puppeteer behind a white cloth screen lit by lamps, creating dramatic shadows.

Wayang usually tells epic stories, as well as local stories that contain deep moral and philosophical values. This performance is accompanied by set of traditional music instruments, with puppeteer's narration, songs, and dialogues between characters that bring a magical and profound nuance.

In addition to being entertainment, wayang has spiritual and educational meanings, often used in traditional events, religious celebrations, and art performances. Wayang is really unique and extraordinary artistic and historical value.
